# Verify on Deployed Site Only

All verification and testing for this project must be done **only** against the deployed production site.

## Rule

- **Test and verify ONLY via:** https://www.australianrates.com (production).
- **Do NOT** run or rely on local dev servers, localhost, or local builds for acceptance or verification of front-end or full-stack behaviour.
- Use `npm run verify:prod -- --scope=auto --depth=smoke` for default production verification, `npm run verify:prod -- --scope=full --depth=full` for full sign-off, and `node diagnose-api.js` when you need deeper production API triage.
- Local dev (`npm run dev:api`, `wrangler pages dev`, etc.) is for development only; it must not be used as the source of truth for “does it work”.

## Rationale

Production is the only environment that reflects the real deploy (Cloudflare Pages, Workers, DNS, and config). Verifying there ensures the fix or feature actually works for users.
